<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-09-30T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-09-30T17:00:00-05:00" n="412" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d412">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.63/5a</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Chargé <persName type="to">Mayer</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-09-30T17:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 30, 1916, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your September 22, 6 p.m. In cooperation with Ruan you may inform Haitian
                            Government that, in view of last clause Article II of treaty, this
                            Government believes that, in the program of economic and domestic
                            rehabilitation, it is of the utmost importance that all <pb facs="0438" n="362" xml:id="pg_362"/> matters relative to concessions, and
                            consequently affecting national finances and resources, be submitted to
                            Financial Adviser for his recommendations.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>